 </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle6">How to clean the electric kettle?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Wash the kettle by hand with washing liquid and fresh water, scrub with a sponge until the entire kettle is clean. If you feel a sponge may damage the kettle, alternatively used a soft cloth to wash it. Once it has been washed, leave it to completely dry before you plug it in and next use.
</div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle7">Can I make tea or coffee?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Electric kettle is recommended only to boil water. You can use this water to make tea, coffee.
      </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle8">Can I cook Maggie noodles in the electric kettle?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">No. Wonderchef Electric kettle is recommended only to boil water. You can use this hot water to make tea, coffee, soup. 
      </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle9">Can I stop the electric kettle in between the operation?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Yes. Wonderchef Electrical Kettle comes with an on/off switch. To stop the kettle once desired water temp of water is reached, you can switch off the kettle.
      </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle10">Can I carry it with me on holiday?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Yes definitely. Wonderchef Electric Kettle is portable and light weight and can easily be carried when u travel for holiday.
      </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle11">What is the warranty period?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Wonderchef Electric Kettle comes with a 1 year warranty.</div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle12">Can I boil milk in electric kettle?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Electric kettle is recommended only to boil water. You can use this water to make tea, coffee.
      </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle13">Is the lid made up of steel or plastic?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">The lid of Wonderchef Electric kettle is made of special grade plastic which can withstand heat. </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle14">How strong is the glass vessel?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Wonderchef Azure kettle is made of borosilicate glass. Borosilicate is the best glass material as it can withstand high temperature and not easily breakable. However, if enough force is used or the kettle falls, it might break.
      </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle15">How does the electric kettle work?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Inside each Kettle is a metal coil called heating element. When the kettle is switched on, electrical energy travels through the coil, heating the coil which in turn brings the cold water inside the kettle to boiling point. Further the kettles are fitted with a thermostat, which then auto shuts off the kettle once boiling point is reached.
      </div>
    </dd>
   <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle16">How can I control the temperature in electric kettle?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">There is no switch to control the temperature in electric kettle. The kettle will automatically shut down when water is boiled. 
      </div>
    </dd>
  <dt class="acc_trigger specic_tab"><a href="#toggle17">Can I detach the chord and base from the electric kettle?</a></dt>
    <dd class="acc_container">
        <div class="block">Yes, the Wonderchef electric kettle rests on a 360 degrees cordless and detachable power base. The Kettle rests on the base and is detachable for convenient usage and portability. Power is supplied to the kettle only when it is placed on the base. The base of the kettle is connected via chord to the electricity source. 
      </div>
    </dd>
